## How to Work (follow this exactly)

1. Iterate through all pending code generation and test generation tasks
2. For each service with a pending **code_gen** task:
   a. Generate the handler/entry-point code for the service (language and service type are specified in the task)
   b. Validate the generated code for syntax correctness
   c. If syntax errors are found, attempt to fix them (up to the configured retry limit)
   d. On success, mark the task as done and store the generated file
3. After completing code for a service, generate its tests:
   a. Generate unit tests that cover the handler code just produced
   b. Validate and fix syntax the same way as for code generation
   c. On success, mark the task as done and store the test file
4. Continue until all tasks are done or failed

## Rules
- Always complete **code_gen before test_gen** for each service — tests depend on the generated handler code
- If code generation fails for a service, skip its test generation — mark the test task as failed with a clear reason
- Prioritize services that other services depend on — check the architecture overview for dependency order
- When all tasks are done or failed, stop — do not generate extra files or improvise
